        public void startRecording(RecorderConfiguration configuration)
        Description copied from interface: IDataRecorder
        Starts recording using the given recorder configuration.

        In order to be able to start recording, this recorder needs to be enabled first (see IDataRecorder.enable(RecorderConfiguration)).

        Note that there is no guarantee about when precisely the recording will be started. If the recording should start at a specific point in time precisely, use the IDataRecorder with a trigger action (StartRecordingAction) instead.

      • getConfiguration

        public RecorderConfiguration getConfiguration()
        Description copied from interface: IDataRecorder
        Returns the configuration.
      • If the recorder is enabled then the current configuration is returned.
      • If the recorder is not enabled then the previous configuration is returned.
      • If the recorder has no previous configuration then null is returned.

  • enable

    public void enable(RecorderConfiguration configuration)
    Description copied from interface: IDataRecorder
    Enables the data recorder with the given recorder configuration.

    This does not start the recording process. Enabled means that the recorder is ready to start recording. A disable process occurs automatically when the recorder stops. This means that the same recorder must be enabled again in order to record data.

    Specified by:
    enable in interface IDataRecorder
    Parameters:
    configuration - the recorder configuration to enable the data recorder with

  • isEnabled

    public boolean isEnabled()
    Description copied from interface: IDataRecorder
    Provides the state of the recording process.
    Specified by:
    isEnabled in interface IDataRecorder
    Returns:
    true if recording is enabled, false otherwise.

    true if the SPR-state of the data recording SPR is at least SPRState.PREPARING but not SPRState.MAINTAINING or further yet, false otherwise.
